      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KENISIS (8) improved out of sight last start when facing the starter for just the second time, making up plenty of late ground to finish second over 1350m at the Beaumont track. Should make further progress at this early stage of her career and in a modest line-up she looks the testing material. VELKA (5) registered a third minor placing from four runs this prep when an eye-catching second over 1200m at Mudgee last time out. A few things look favourable today - longer trip, better gate, blinkers on. Serious threat. PEAR BELLINI (7) added to her long list of placings when a close second over the mile at this track last Tuesday. Coming back in trip is the obvious query but she is well in with the claim and very honest. TOKE (4) worked home in good fashion but was never a winning hope over 1200m at Tamworth recently. Enjoys a soft run from gate one and should be thereabouts again. CLASS REVOLUTION (1) is fitter for two runs back and can sneak onto the semaphore board.",
